  "commentary": "With SPX at 6783.62 sitting right at the GEX flip point of 6783, dealers are in a critical transition zone where they'll aggressively sell any move toward the massive 6800 gamma wall (88.2B) while providing support on dips toward 6770 (-20.6B negative gamma). The PIN regime combined with the detected wall break and GEX surge suggests dealers are actively hedging large gamma positions, creating strong mean-reverting forces that should cap upside momentum near 6790-6800 and provide buying interest on any flush below current levels. Watch 6800 as the key resistance where dealer selling intensifies and 6770 as the support level where dealer buying kicks in.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pinned between 6770-6800 with choppy mean-reverting action.",
